HEADWORD: Oppilation
<hw>Op`pi*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>oppilatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>opilation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act
of filling or crowding together; a stopping by redundant matter;
obstruction, particularly in the lower intestines.</def> <rj><au>Jer.
Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

